import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Year').sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Disasters', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['Disasters'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    disaster_counts = data.groupby('Disaster Type')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    disaster_counts = disaster_counts.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='Disaster Type', y='count', data=disaster_counts, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('Which type of natural disaster is the most frequent?', wrap=True)
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'] = data['Deaths'].fillna(0)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Deaths', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by natural disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby(['Country']).sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.barplot(x='Country', y='count', data=data, ax=ax)
    plt.title('Which countries are most affected by natural disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Disaster Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['Year', 'Disaster Type'])['Economic Damage (US$)'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Year', y='Economic Damage (US$)', hue='Disaster Type', data=data, palette='bright')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the economic impact of natural disasters?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
